article.headline: Nicholls wins 67-64 over Southeastern Louisiana
article.description: — Byron Ireland had 15 points in Nicholls State's 67-64 win against Southeastern Louisiana on Thursday night.
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. -- — Byron Ireland had 15 points in Nicholls State's 67-64 win against Southeastern Louisiana on Thursday night. Ireland added three steals for the Colonels (5-4, 1-0 Southland Conference). Jamal West scored 13 points and added 10 rebounds. Michael Gray Jr. shot 4 for 11 to finish with 10 points, while adding six rebounds. Sam Hines Jr. led the Lions (4-5, 0-1) in scoring, finishing with 13 points, 11 rebounds and four assists. Brody Rowbury added 13 points and eight rebounds for SE Louisiana. Jakevion Buckley also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
